text.section:
This title shall be liberally construed and applied to promote its underlying purposes and policies to:
Support and facilitate the realization of the full potential of computer information transactions;
Clarify the law governing computer information transactions;
Enable expanding commercial practice in computer information transactions by commercial usage and agreement of the parties;
Promote uniformity of the law with respect to the subject matter of this title among states that enact it; and
Permit the continued expansion of commercial practices in the excluded transactions through custom, usage, and agreement of the parties.
